{"word":"κήδω","slug":"κήδω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κήδω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>κεκαδήσομαι</el> from <a href='S:κήδω'><el>κήδω</el></a>, for <el>κεκαδήσω, κέκαδον</el>, <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:χάζω'><el>χάζω</el></a> II\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> <i>to trouble, distress, vex</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> and <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be troubled</i> or <i>distressed for</i> others, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <el>τῶν ἀλφίτων</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> in <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>κηδόμενος, η, ον</el>, <i>caring for</i> a person, <i>anxious</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}